- content_for :page_title do
  ' The Startup Alliance Foundation

- content_for :page_header do
  h2.bold.little-space-top.little-space-bottom.white-text.text-center
    ' The Startup Alliance Foundation

.row
  .medium-8.medium-offset-2.columns
    p.snug-top.space-bottom.text-right
      ' Working to accelerate the globalization of entrepreneurship.
    p.snug-top.show-for-medium &nbsp;

    h5.bold.space-top
      ' We believe
    p.little-snug-top
      ' Entrepreneurship is one of the greatest drivers of good in this world.
      ' Entrepreneurs are a primary source of innovation, job and value creation
      ' for themselves, their families and their communities.
      '
    h5.bold.space-top
      ' Accordingly
    p.little-snug-top
      ' We engage in philanthropic activities to favorably impact the landscape in support of
      ' entrepreneurs worldwide.
      ' Additionally, we work to spread knowledge and skills through educational efforts
      ' both directly to entrepreneurs and through various Entrepreneurship Support
      ' Organizations (ESOs) and conferences.
      '

    h5.bold.space-top
      ' What we do
    p.little-snug-top
      ' The Startup Alliance Foundation is engaged in three philanthropic activities:
      '
    ul.snug-top
      li
        span.bold
          ' Policy Development —
        ' Unlocking the power of entrepreneurship to bolster economies, create jobs and
        ' build more vibrant communities requires sensible regulation and governance.
        ' The Startup Alliance foundation works with national, regional and local governments and NGOs to
        ' make sure the right conditions exist for their people to build successful and sustainable companies.
        '
      li
        span.bold
          ' Educational Outreach —
        ' We sponsor experts in the science of startup success to deliver their knowledge to
        ' entrepreneurs without regard to skill level or the type of busienss they operate.
        ' We also sponsor various in person entrepreneur gatherings plus local and
        ' regional entrepreneurship conferences.
        '
      li
        span.bold
          ' Directed ESO Grants —
        ' Startup Alliance makes cash grants to a variety of Entrepreneurship Support Organizations worldwide.
        ' This includes launch assistance and the ongoing support of both governmental and non-governmental ESOs whose
        ' mission aligns with ours.
        '


